{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"de16f9c06fb55838","type":"group","x":-968,"y":-573,"width":1796,"height":1405,"label":"Goal nodes"},
		{"id":"1127b953ee03f762","type":"text","text":"Goal nodes are a more advanced feature, and you'll have to install some things using your terminal. If you're unsure or you have some questions, ask your favorite LLM or ask us in the [discord](https://discord.gg/jDJTu5ea).","x":-369,"y":-719,"width":569,"height":118},
		{"id":"33631d02eec59c40","type":"text","text":"This is a goal node. It is a kind of action node that leverages [MCP](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/getting-started/intro) to provide the LLM with tools defined by third party MCP server authors.\n\nThe goal node will utilize relevant MCP servers from your cannoli settings to achieve the goal defined in the code block.\n\nGoal nodes require usage of the cannoli server, which is a companion application that makes MCP servers available to cannolis executing inside Obsidian.","x":-921,"y":-531,"width":439,"height":307},
		{"id":"ec4f6e82c79efa3a","type":"text","text":"","x":-440,"y":58,"width":781,"height":728,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"8b3cfbb075627ed9","type":"text","text":"```mcp\nYou are an agent inside of an obsidian vault, executing one part of a script. Below is the current configuration for the mcp-mcp tool. If you suggest other configurations, make them fit this format:\n\n{\n  \"name\": \"mcp-mcp\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"type\": \"stdio\",\n  \"command\": \"uvx\",\n  \"args\": [\n    \"mcp-mcp\"\n  ],\n  \"env\": {}\n}\n\nPlease find an mcp server that can help me find me manage my obsidian vault. Write me the config JSON block if you can find the necessary info. If you use fetch to get more content, make sure you read enough to find the MCP config block.\n```","x":-429,"y":-545,"width":759,"height":547,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"8ab9329ec0c32c9e","type":"text","text":"This goal node is a bit meta. It uses the \"mcp-mcp\" MCP server (lol) to search a public registry of MCP servers and find relevant ones.\n\nIf you like the one it finds, you can add it to your MCP settings on the cannoli settings pane!","x":356,"y":-436,"width":443,"height":183},
		{"id":"f842e49cd8d0759d","type":"text","text":"To try this cannoli, you first have to start up your cannoli server. You can do this by following the directions in the cannoli server section of the cannoli settings pane.\n\nThe MCP servers we'll be using require the [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) python package manager/runtime. There are a lot of MCP servers which use uv, so it's a good idea to install it now. You can install it easily [here](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/)\n\nOnce your server is running and connected, you'll want to connect two MCP servers using the configurations below:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"mcp-mcp\",\n  \"name\": \"mcp-mcp\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"type\": \"stdio\",\n  \"command\": \"uvx\",\n  \"args\": [\n    \"mcp-mcp\"\n  ],\n  \"env\": {}\n}\n```\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"fetch\",\n  \"name\": \"fetch\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"type\": \"stdio\",\n  \"command\": \"uvx\",\n  \"args\": [\n    \"mcp-server-fetch\"\n  ],\n  \"env\": {}\n}\n```\n\nNow you're ready to run it!","x":-920,"y":-168,"width":438,"height":971}
	],
